    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-24T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-24T02:00:00-05:00" n="1410"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1410">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.4552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Callanan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-24T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 24, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:40 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>193. Registration Consular cars refused today unless submitted as for “former
                    American Consulate General” and “former Consul “General”. British colleague only
                    other similar case same treatment. Registration in personal name without
                    reference to status refused. Possibilities under consideration with Embassy’s
                    65, February 26, to Peiping<note n="70" xml:id="d1410fn70">Not found in
                        Department of State files.</note> in mind and no intention denying Consular
                    status.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 193; repeated Nanking 148, OffEmb Canton 89.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Callanan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
